  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Let's define a good tree:\n\nIt is a tree with **k * n** nodes labeled from **0** to **k * n - 1**\nNode **i** and node **j** are not adjacent, for all **0 &lt;= i, j &lt; k * n** such that **i div k = j div k** (here **div** means integer division.  E.g. 7 **div** 2 = 3)\n\nGiven **n** and **k**, how many different good trees are there?",
    "constraints": [],
    "inputFormat": "Two integers **n(1 &lt;= n &lt;= 10^5), k(1&lt;= k &lt;=3)**",
    "outputFormat": "Output the number of different good trees. As the result may be very large, just output the remainder when divided by (10^9 + 7).",
